2 Killed , 45 Injured in Road Accident in Bangladesh
DHAKA , November 22 ( Xinhua ) -- Two people were killed and 45 others were injured , including five children , in a traffic accident Sunday afternoon in southeastern Bangladesh 's hill district of Rangamati .
The accident occurred when a loaded bus heading for Rangamati fell into a 120 feet roadside ditch , the BSS news agency reported .
It was not known immediately what had caused the accident .
Local fire brigade personnel , police and servicemen rushed to the scene after the accident , and recovered two bodies and rescued 45 passengers with injures , police said .
Ten seriously injured passengers were sent to a Chittagong hospital , and some others were admitted to the Rangamati General Hospital .
